This is a rich, hearty and warm red wine pot roast that you will keep coming back to throughout the year.  This recipe won’t result in chewy meat. It is cooked in a sauce of beef broth, red wine and a generous helping of butter.  Notes This recipe works for a 3-5 pound pot roast, but the cooking times will vary. At 300°F (148.8 °C) in a covered Dutch oven, cook the red wine pot roast for 3-5 hours depending on the size of your meat.  This recipe can be found on oursaltykitch.com.